/*                        CONSTRUCTOR

1) It is used for member variable initialization.
2) When we create an object of class then compiler automatically calls constructor.
3) If user do not creates any constructor in a class then compoiler automatically creates a default constructor in class.
4)constructur name and class name must be same.
5) Do not define datatype to constructor, and do not return value in a constructor.


**TYPES OF CONSTRUCTOR**
    
1) DEFAULT CONSTRUCTOR
            i) complie creates
            ii) user creates
2) PARAMATERISED
            i) Demo(int a, float b)
               {
                   ------
                   ------
               }
3) COPY 
        i) Demo(int a, float b)
           {
               ------
               ------
           }
4) DEFAULT ARGUMENTS
        i) Demo(int a, float b=7.9)
           {
               ------
               ------
           }
5) DYNAMIC
        i) Demo(int a*)
        {
            must use new operator in logic.-------
        }
            
            
            
note:   
            class Demo
            {
                public:
                    demo(int a, float b)
                    {
                        cout<<a<<" "<<b<<endl;
                    }
            };
            demo x=demo(7, 9.4)
            or 
            demo x(7, 9.4)

            

                DYNAMIC CONSTRUCTOR

    ---> user new operator in constructor defination
            i.e: a= (int *)malloc(5*sizeof(int));
                  a=new int[5];

        
        for deletion of memory
        int *a;
        free(a);     //in c
        delete(a);   //in cpp
